2012-12-24|2012-12-30.description: "What Happened Was?" part 1 of 3! When Calendar Man and Batman battle during a Gotham Knights game, things go very, very wrong. But with everyone in the crowd giving a different eye witness account, will the GCPD even be able to figure out what happened?
2012-12-24|2012-12-30.name: What Happened Was..., Part 1 of 3

2012-01-30|2012-02-05.description: After last issue's startling revelations at The Dam, the girls struggle to survive as Jepperd learns the truth about Project Evergreen. But can he make it back in time to save them? And even if he does, how will he get inside the impenetrable Dam? "Unnatural Habitats" amps up and heads toward a stunning conclusion you'll never see coming!
2012-01-30|2012-02-05.name: Unnatural Habitats, Part Two

2012-02-13|2012-02-19.description:
Yoshimori’s absentee mother, Sumiko, makes an unexpected appearance at Karasumori—but not for a tearful family reunion. Sumiko leads Yoshimori and Tokine through a labyrinth to find and remove the mystical site’s mysterious guardian...

What does Sumiko know of the circumstances surrounding Tokine’s father’s death? Can she be trusted? Can Karasumori’s guardian be trusted...?

And what fate awaits Karasumori if its guardian leaves?!
2012-02-13|2012-02-19.name: Vol. 30

2012-02-27|2012-03-04.description:
Wolverine leads X-Force into their deadliest mission yet: kill Apocalypse, or die trying! But what they find splits the team apart and sets them against each other!

By Rick Remender and Jerome Openal.

Also: Deadpool encounters Steve Rogers and his Secret Avengers, and gets a job offer! But supervillain psychiatrist Doctor Bong plans to destroy them all!

By Daniel Way and Carlo Barben.

Includes material reprinted from Uncanny X-Force #3-4, and Deadpool #28.

2012-03-19|2012-03-25.description:
Your complete guide to the award-winning BBC One series!

Written and researched by Andrew Pixley.

The 2011 season of Doctor Who began in the most dramatic way possible – by killing off the Doctor in the first episode! Unaware of his ultimate fate, the Doctor (Matt Smith) was reunited with his friends, newlyweds Amy (Karen Gillan) and Rory Pond (Arthur Darvill) and together they embarked on an incredible series of adventures in time and space. Their journey took them from the acid mines in the future to the empty world of Apalapucia, and saw encounters with Headless monks, Handbots, living dolls... and even Adolf Hitler!

Now, Doctor Who Magazine takes you behind the scenes of these astonishing episodes with an in-depth episode guide – including original storylines, deleted scenes, media appearances, ratings information and hundreds of facts about the day-to-day life of the making of Doctor Who – all illustrated with gorgeous, never-before-seen photographs. This collectors’ edition examines The Rebel Flesh, The Almost People, A Good Man Goes to War, Let's Kill Hitler, Night Terrors and The Girl Who Waited, as well as the specially-made Doctor Who sequence that introduced the National Television Awards.

This is your essential guide to the worlds of Doctor Who. Get ready to discover a wealth of information – and remember, silence will fall …
2012-03-19|2012-03-25.name: The Doctor Who Companion: The Eleventh: Volume Four

2012-04-09|2012-04-15.description:
Tokyo trembles as Hope and the new mutant generation take on the mad artist Kenji!

Also: The X-Men fall victim to a mysterious illness, and Cyclops is forced to place Utopia Island under quarantine. But the sinister Lobe has the answer: a brand new team of X-Men!

By Matt Fraction and Greg Land

Includes material reprinted from Generation Hope #3 and Uncanny X-Men #530-531.

2012-05-07|2012-05-13.description: The case of the citizens of Arkham City versus Joker BEGINS! Judge Harvey Dent calls many witnesses for the prosecution to the stand to argue in favor of convicting Joker...but Joker has a key ally as his defense attorney. When it comes time to deliberate, the jury's interrupted by a surprise, last minute witness!
2012-05-07|2012-05-13.name: Clown Court: Part 2

2012-05-14|2012-05-20.description:
Both issues tie-in to AVENGERS VS. X-MEN!

The Utopia and Gen Hope teens have come to the Academy…as prisoners?

Sebastian Shaw strikes!

Guest-starring Wolverine, Hawkeye, Hercules and Captain America!
2012-05-14|2012-05-20.name: Protective Services, Part 2

2012-06-11|2012-06-17.description: When a new race of mutants is discovered, Storm and her team take to the skies to get an in depth look, but they may just get more than they anticipated!
2012-06-11|2012-06-17.name: Blank Generation, Part 1

2012-06-11|2012-06-17.description: The final issue of what MTV Called, 'One of the Best Ongoing Comic Book Series!' The end has come for comics' favorite anti-hero, Max Damage, but not before an explosive conclusion that will leave fans reeling and finally answer the question - can someone truly be Incorruptible? Don't miss the incredible last issue of the companion to Mark Waid's Eisner-nominated superhero series, Irredeemable!

2012-07-09|2012-07-15.description: The Empress sleeps alone while all around her find comfort, she reconsiders her vows, and holds a Tournament of Kings. Every throne needs an heir, after all.

2012-08-20|2012-08-26.description: Max Fury has been captured! The truth behind the Shadow Council's ultimate plot! The new Masters of Evil strike! Black Widow knows who the traitor is, but can she get to her teammates in time to save them from his schemes?
2012-08-20|2012-08-26.name: Something Wicked This Way Comes

2012-08-27|2012-09-02.description: It's all built to this: FINAL EXECUTION enters its last act! The new Brotherhood of Evil Mutants makes their move! Fantomex's deceptions come back to haunt the team!
2012-08-27|2012-09-02.name: While You Were Away

2012-08-27|2012-09-02.description: Hunting vampires is thirsty work, but Skinner and Pearl must control their bloodlust as they cross more names off the vampire blacklist. Meanwhile, Henry’s life hangs in the balance! The next AMERICAN VAMPIRE epic continues in “The Blacklist” part three.
2012-08-27|2012-09-02.name: The Blacklist, Part Three of Six

2012-09-10|2012-09-16.name: In The Trenches

2012-09-17|2012-09-23.description: Love in the ruins: Can Hawkeye and Spider-Woman's budding romance last amidst the end of the world?
2012-09-17|2012-09-23.name: Ready! Aim...

2012-10-22|2012-10-28.description: Old man Prophet's team goes looking for supplies on a city built into the torso of a giant at war with its other body parts. And an old acquaintance.
2012-10-22|2012-10-28.name: [untitled]

2012-10-22|2012-10-28.description: In a risky attempt to get to the Eye of the World, Moiraine has talked the Loial into taking the group to The Ways - mystical transportation aids tainted by darkness. It's a risk the Ogier is uncomfortable with, but that Moiraine sees as necessary... especially after the Dark One again visits the dreams of Rand, Mat, and Perrin. Time is running out for our heroes in the latest installment of Robert Jordan's THE WHEEL OF TIME: THE EYE OF THE WORLD!

volume.name: Robert Jordan's Wheel of Time: The Eye of the World

2012-10-29|2012-11-04.description: A new villain has arrived in Century City. Gravilov is a high-tech arms dealer, bent on using Green Hornet's city as a base from which to ship death worldwide. As Green Hornet and Kato try to stop Gravilov, the fight becomes very personal. Old enemies must become new allies, to save the lives of those dear to Kato.

2012-11-19|2012-11-25.description:
A battle over one hundred years in the making - sister vs. sister! No one gets out unscathed! Not every bodily limb survives!

PLUS: In 1920s Paris, Glory teams and Ernest Hemingway take down the greatest villain the city has ever known, illustrated by New Yorker cartoonist ROMAN MURADOV!
2012-11-19|2012-11-25.name: Bloodshadow, Part Two: Relentless

2012-11-19|2012-11-25.description: Grab your wallets, it's time for a SHOPPING SPREE!
2012-11-19|2012-11-25.name: Betty & Veronica $hopping $pree!

"SPACE CAKES," Conclusion

The bonus-sized wedding issue, CHEW's half-way point, and the issue that is gonna take EVERYBODY by surprise. Sure, it's a terrible jumping-on point for new readers, but did we mention the FREE TRI-FOLD POSTER COVER, at no extra cost?
